   3, 'If the compensating balance is not legally restricted, the funds remain available and are included in cash; the arrangement is disclosed. Only legally restricted balances are segregated from cash.', 2),
  ('FAR', 'Cash & Cash Equivalents',
   'An entity''s book balance is P300,000. The bank statement reveals a credit memo of P50,000 for a note collected by the bank, a service charge of P1,000, and a customer NSF check of P9,000. The adjusted cash balance is:',
   'P240,000', 'P260,000', 'P340,000', 'P360,000',
   2, 'Adjusted book balance = P300,000 + P50,000 note collected − P1,000 service charge − P9,000 NSF = P340,000. All three items are book reconciling items requiring adjusting entries.', 2),
  ('FAR', 'Receivables',
   'An entity estimates doubtful accounts at 1% of credit sales. Credit sales were P5,000,000 and the allowance for doubtful accounts had a P20,000 credit balance before adjustment. Doubtful accounts expense for the year is:',
   'P30,000', 'P50,000', 'P70,000', 'P100,000',
