  ('FAR', 'Receivables',
   'Writing off a specific account against the allowance for doubtful accounts:',
   'Has no effect on the net realizable value of accounts receivable', 'Decreases the net realizable value of accounts receivable', 'Increases doubtful accounts expense', 'Decreases total current assets',
   0, 'The write-off reduces gross receivables and the allowance by the same amount, so net realizable value — and expense — are unaffected. The expense was recognized earlier when the allowance was established.', 1),
  ('FAR', 'Receivables',
   'The collection of an account previously written off under the allowance method:',
   'Increases doubtful accounts expense', 'Has no effect on the allowance for doubtful accounts', 'Increases the allowance for doubtful accounts', 'Increases net income in the period of collection',
   2, 'The recovery reinstates the account (debit AR, credit allowance) and records the collection (debit cash, credit AR). The net effect is an increase in cash and in the allowance; no income is recognized.', 2),
  ('FAR', 'Receivables',
   'An entity sold goods in exchange for a P1,000,000 three-year noninterest-bearing note when the market rate was 10% (PV factor of 1 at 10% for 3 periods = 0.7513). Interest income for the first year is:',
   'P0', 'P75,130', 'P100,000', 'P248,700',
   1, 'The note is initially recorded at P1,000,000 × 0.7513 = P751,300. First-year interest income under the effective interest method = P751,300 × 10% = P75,130, amortizing the discount toward face value.', 2),
  ('FAR', 'Receivables',
   'An entity sold used equipment and received a two-year note bearing 3% interest when the prevailing market rate for similar notes was 12%. The sale price (and initial measurement of the note) is best measured at:',
   'The face amount of the note', 'The face amount plus total interest at 3%', 'The maturity value of the note', 'The present value of all note cash flows discounted at 12%',
   3, 'When the stated rate is unreasonably low relative to the market rate, the note is initially measured at present value using the market (imputed) rate, which represents the cash price equivalent of the equipment sold.', 2),
  ('FAR', 'Receivables',
   'In a factoring arrangement, the factor''s holdback (amount withheld to cover expected sales returns and allowances) is reported by the seller as:',
   'A receivable from the factor', 'A loss on factoring', 'An offset against accounts payable', 'Interest expense of the period',
   0, 'The holdback is the seller''s residual claim collectible from the factor once returns and allowances are settled, so it is a receivable (commonly ''receivable from factor''), not an expense or loss.', 2),
  ('FAR', 'Receivables',
   'A P600,000, one-year note bearing 12% interest was discounted at a bank at 15% six months before maturity. The proceeds from discounting are:',
   'P600,000', 'P621,600', 'P636,000', 'P672,000',
