  ('FAR', 'Receivables',
   'When a note receivable is discounted with a bank on a without-recourse basis, the transaction is:',
   'A secured borrowing, with the note remaining on the books', 'A conditional sale requiring disclosure of a contingent liability', 'An outright sale of the note, with no contingent liability', 'Recorded only by a memorandum entry',
   2, 'Without recourse, the bank assumes the risk of nonpayment; the transferor derecognizes the note and recognizes a gain or loss, with no contingent liability. With recourse, the transfer is a conditional sale (contingent liability disclosed) or a secured borrowing.', 2),
  ('FAR', 'Receivables',
   'Loan origination fees received by a bank from a borrower are:',
   'Recognized as fee income when the loan is released', 'Credited directly to retained earnings', 'Recognized as income evenly over the loan term', 'Deducted from the initial carrying amount of the loan and recognized over the term as an adjustment of the effective yield',
   3, 'Origination fees are integral to the effective interest rate: they reduce the loan''s initial carrying amount and are amortized into interest income over the term, recalibrating the yield (direct origination costs have the opposite effect).', 3),
  ('FAR', 'Receivables',
   'Under the PFRS 9 simplified approach, the loss allowance for trade receivables without a significant financing component is measured at:',
