  ('FAR', 'Inventories',
   'Which statement about the FIFO cost formula is correct?',
   'It produces the same ending inventory whether a periodic or perpetual system is used', 'It produces a higher ending inventory under the perpetual system than the periodic system', 'It assigns the most recent costs to cost of goods sold', 'It is prohibited for inventories that are ordinarily interchangeable',
   0, 'Under FIFO, the earliest costs always exit first regardless of when sales are recorded, so periodic and perpetual FIFO yield identical ending inventory and cost of goods sold. (It is weighted average that differs between systems.)', 2),
  ('FAR', 'Inventories',
   'An entity began the period with 200 units at P50, then purchased 300 units at P60 and 500 units at P66. It sold 600 units during the period. Under the weighted average (periodic) method, ending inventory is:',
   'P20,000', 'P24,400', 'P26,400', 'P27,000',
