  ('FAR', 'Inventories',
   'A fire destroyed an entity''s warehouse. Records show beginning inventory P500,000, purchases P2,500,000, and sales P3,000,000. The gross profit rate is 25% of sales. Goods costing P50,000 were saved from the fire. The estimated fire loss is:',
   'P550,000', 'P600,000', 'P700,000', 'P750,000',
   2, 'Cost of goods sold = 75% × P3,000,000 = P2,250,000. Estimated ending inventory = P500,000 + P2,500,000 − P2,250,000 = P750,000, less P50,000 salvaged = P700,000 fire loss.', 3),
  ('FAR', 'Inventories',
   'Under the conservative (conventional) retail inventory method, the cost-to-retail ratio is computed by:',
   'Including both net markups and net markdowns', 'Excluding both net markups and net markdowns', 'Including net markdowns but excluding net markups', 'Including net markups but excluding net markdowns',
   3, 'The conservative approach includes net markups but excludes net markdowns from the ratio''s denominator, producing a lower ratio and an ending inventory that approximates the lower of average cost and net realizable value.', 3),
  ('FAR', 'Inventories',
   'A reversal of a prior inventory write-down to net realizable value is:',
