   2, 'Consigned goods remain the consignor''s inventory until sold by the consignee, and the freight to place them at the consignee''s location is a cost of bringing inventory to its present location, so it is inventoriable.', 2),
  ('FAR', 'Inventories',
   'An entity purchased two lots of inventory for a lump sum of P6,000,000. Lot A has a sales value of P2,000,000 and Lot B of P6,000,000. The cost allocated to Lot A is:',
   'P1,500,000', 'P2,000,000', 'P3,000,000', 'P4,500,000',
   0, 'Under the relative sales value method, Lot A receives P6,000,000 × (P2,000,000 ÷ P8,000,000) = P1,500,000. Allocating equally or by individual sales value alone would misstate cost.', 2),
  ('FAR', 'Inventories',
   'Which cost formula is NOT permitted by PAS 2?',
   'Specific identification', 'First-in, first-out', 'Last-in, first-out', 'Weighted average',
   2, 'PAS 2 permits specific identification (required for items not ordinarily interchangeable), FIFO, and weighted average. LIFO was eliminated and is prohibited.', 1),
  ('FAR', 'Inventories',
   'Goods purchased in transit at year-end (FOB shipping point) were recorded as purchases, but were excluded from the physical count and from ending inventory. The effect on the current year is:',
   'Net income is overstated', 'Cost of goods sold is understated', 'Working capital is unaffected', 'Cost of goods sold is overstated and net income is understated',
   3, 'Including the purchase but omitting the goods from ending inventory inflates cost of goods sold (beginning + purchases − understated ending), thereby understating both net income and current assets.', 2)
)
insert into public.questions (topic_id, stem, choices, correct_index, explanation, difficulty)
select t.id, q.stem, jsonb_build_array(q.a, q.b, q.c, q.d), q.correct_index, q.explanation, q.difficulty
from q join t on t.code = q.subject_code and lower(t.name) = lower(q.topic)
where not exists (select 1 from public.questions x where x.stem = q.stem);

-- ===== far-batch-003 =====
-- Generated from content/far-batch-003.csv by scripts/csv-to-seed-sql.mjs — do not edit by hand.
-- Idempotent: skips any question whose stem already exists.
with t as (
  select tp.id, tp.name, s.code from public.topics tp
  join public.subjects s on s.id = tp.subject_id
),
q(subject_code, topic, stem, a, b, c, d, correct_index, explanation, difficulty) as (values
  ('FAR', 'Property, Plant & Equipment',
   'An item of PPE was acquired on a deferred payment plan extending beyond normal credit terms. The asset is recorded at:',
   'Its cash price equivalent, with the excess of total payments recognized as interest expense over the credit period', 'The total of all payments to be made', 'The total payments less any residual value', 'The first installment paid',
   0, 'When payment is deferred beyond normal credit terms, cost is the cash price equivalent (present value); the difference between that amount and total payments is interest expense over the period of credit, unless capitalized under PAS 23.', 2),
  ('FAR', 'Property, Plant & Equipment',
   'An entity constructed a machine for its own use at a total cost lower than the price quoted by outside suppliers. The saving is:',
   'Recognized as income in the year of completion', 'Credited to a revaluation surplus', 'Not recognized — the asset is simply recorded at its actual cost of construction', 'Deducted from depreciation over the asset''s life',
   2, 'Self-constructed assets are measured at the actual directly attributable costs of construction. Internal ''profit'' or savings versus an outside purchase price is never recognized as income or equity.', 2),
  ('FAR', 'Property, Plant & Equipment',
   'Under PAS 20, a government grant related to a depreciable asset may be presented as:',
   'Either deferred income amortized over the asset''s life, or a deduction from the asset''s carrying amount', 'Direct credit to retained earnings', 'Immediate income upon receipt in all cases', 'Share premium from government contribution',
   0, 'Grants related to assets are presented either as deferred income recognized in profit or loss over the asset''s useful life, or by deducting the grant from the asset''s carrying amount (reducing depreciation). Immediate income or equity treatment is prohibited.', 2),
  ('FAR', 'Property, Plant & Equipment',
   'A government grant is recognized only when there is reasonable assurance that:',
   'The grant has been received in cash', 'The entity will generate taxable income against the grant', 'The government will not request repayment within five years', 'The entity will comply with the conditions attaching to the grant and the grant will be received',
   3, 'PAS 20 requires reasonable assurance on both counts — compliance with conditions and receipt — before recognition. Receipt of cash alone is not conclusive, as conditions may remain unfulfilled.', 2),
  ('FAR', 'Property, Plant & Equipment',
