   0, 'Revenue requires the customer to have obtained control despite the seller''s physical possession — demonstrated by the four bill-and-hold criteria. Custodial services may be a separate performance obligation.', 3),
  ('FAR', 'Revenue Recognition (PFRS 15)',
   'An entity sells goods with a right of return. At the point of sale, the entity recognizes:',
   'Revenue for the full amount, with returns expensed when they occur', 'No revenue until the return period lapses', 'Revenue only for the consideration it expects to be entitled to, a refund liability for expected returns, and an asset for the right to recover the goods', 'A provision equal to the gross sales price',
   2, 'Expected returns are variable consideration: revenue is constrained to the expected entitled amount, a refund liability captures expected refunds, and a return asset (measured at former carrying amount less recovery costs) reflects the goods to be recovered.', 2),
  ('FAR', 'Revenue Recognition (PFRS 15)',
   'A consignor recognizes revenue on goods delivered to a consignee (dealer):',
