  ('AFAR', 'Partnership Accounting',
   'Gail retires from a partnership when her capital balance is P350,000; she is paid P410,000 and the bonus method is used. The remaining partners, Hana and Iris, share profits 60:40 between themselves. Hana''s capital was P600,000 before the retirement; immediately after the retirement it is:',
   'P540,000', 'P564,000', 'P576,000', 'P600,000',
   1, 'The P60,000 excess paid to Gail is a bonus charged to the remaining partners 60:40. Hana absorbs P36,000, so her capital becomes P600,000 − P36,000 = P564,000.', 2),
  ('AFAR', 'Partnership Accounting',
