   0, 'The Investment in Branch account on the home office books and the Home Office account on the branch books are reciprocal and should be equal after all adjustments.', 1),
  ('AFAR', 'Home Office & Branch Accounting',
   'The Home Office account on the branch''s books normally has a:',
   'debit balance representing an asset', 'credit balance representing the home office''s equity in the branch', 'zero balance at all times', 'credit balance representing a liability to outside creditors',
   1, 'The Home Office account functions like an equity account on the branch books and normally carries a credit balance representing the home office''s investment in the branch.', 1),
  ('AFAR', 'Home Office & Branch Accounting',
   'When a home office bills merchandise to its branch at an amount above cost, the excess is recorded by the home office in the:',
   'Shipments to Branch account', 'Sales account', 'Allowance for Overvaluation account', 'Branch Net Income account',
   2, 'Billing above cost creates an unrealized markup recorded in the Allowance for Overvaluation of Branch Inventory account on the home office books.', 1),
  ('AFAR', 'Home Office & Branch Accounting',
   'The branch records merchandise received from the home office at:',
   'cost to the home office', 'net realizable value', 'the lower of cost or net realizable value', 'the billed price',
   3, 'The branch records shipments from the home office at the billed price set by the home office, which may include a markup above cost.', 1),
  ('AFAR', 'Home Office & Branch Accounting',
   'Mekong Branch began the year with an Allowance for Overvaluation of P40,000. During the year the home office shipped merchandise billed at P500,000 containing a P100,000 markup. At year-end the allowance related to ending branch inventory was P30,000. The realized overvaluation to be recognized by the home office is:',
   'P70,000', 'P130,000', 'P170,000', 'P110,000',
   3, 'Realized overvaluation = beginning allowance + markup on shipments − ending allowance = P40,000 + P100,000 − P30,000 = P110,000.', 2),
  ('AFAR', 'Home Office & Branch Accounting',
   'Yangtze Branch reported net income of P250,000 on its own books. The home office computed realized overvaluation of P90,000 for the year. The true (adjusted) branch net income from the home office perspective is:',
   'P160,000', 'P250,000', 'P340,000', 'P430,000',
   2, 'True branch net income = reported net income + realized overvaluation = P250,000 + P90,000 = P340,000.', 2),
  ('AFAR', 'Home Office & Branch Accounting',
   'On December 31, the home office Investment in Branch account shows P820,000, but the branch Home Office account shows P760,000. The only reconciling item is merchandise shipped by the home office, recorded by it but not yet received by the branch. The in-transit merchandise amount is:',
   'P60,000', 'P760,000', 'P820,000', 'P1,580,000',
   0, 'The home office already debited the shipment (raising Investment in Branch) but the branch has not recorded receipt; the difference P820,000 − P760,000 = P60,000 is the in-transit merchandise.', 2),
  ('AFAR', 'Home Office & Branch Accounting',
   'Indus Branch reported net income of P180,000. The Allowance for Overvaluation was P25,000 at the beginning and P15,000 at the end of the year, and shipments during the year carried a markup of P60,000. The true branch net income is:',
   'P110,000', 'P180,000', 'P250,000', 'P260,000',
   2, 'Realized overvaluation = P25,000 + P60,000 − P15,000 = P70,000. True branch net income = P180,000 + P70,000 = P250,000.', 2),
  ('AFAR', 'Home Office & Branch Accounting',
   'The home office bills its branch at 125% of cost. During the year it shipped merchandise that cost P400,000. The markup (overvaluation) included in the shipment is:',
   'P80,000', 'P400,000', 'P500,000', 'P100,000',
   3, 'Billed price = P400,000 × 125% = P500,000. Markup = P500,000 − P400,000 = P100,000.', 2),
  ('AFAR', 'Home Office & Branch Accounting',
   'The home office bills its branch at 120% of cost. The branch''s ending inventory acquired from the home office is recorded at a billed price of P360,000. The allowance for overvaluation related to this ending inventory is:',
   'P60,000', 'P72,000', 'P288,000', 'P300,000',
   0, 'Cost = P360,000 ÷ 120% = P300,000. Allowance for overvaluation = billed price P360,000 − cost P300,000 = P60,000.', 3),
  ('AFAR', 'Home Office & Branch Accounting',
   'The home office ships merchandise to Branch B and pays P15,000 freight. Direct delivery would have cost P9,000; the extra P6,000 arose from first routing the goods through Branch A. The excess freight of P6,000 is:',
   'capitalized by Branch B as part of inventory cost', 'expensed by the home office', 'added to the Allowance for Overvaluation', 'recorded by Branch A as inventory cost',
   1, 'Excess freight from interbranch transfers is treated as an expense of the home office; the receiving branch capitalizes only the normal direct freight of P9,000.', 2),
  ('AFAR', 'Home Office & Branch Accounting',
   'On December 31, the Investment in Branch account is P540,000 and the Home Office account is P575,000. The branch collected P35,000 of a home office receivable and credited Home Office, but the home office has not yet recorded the collection. After this reconciling item, the adjusted reciprocal balance is:',
   'P505,000', 'P540,000', 'P575,000', 'P610,000',
   2, 'The branch credited Home Office for P35,000, raising it to P575,000; the home office must record the same, raising Investment in Branch from P540,000 to P575,000. The adjusted reciprocal balance is P575,000.', 3),
  ('AFAR', 'Home Office & Branch Accounting',
   'Combined net income of a home office and its branch is determined by:',
   'adding the home office own net income and the reported branch net income only', 'adding the home office own net income and the true branch net income (reported plus realized overvaluation)', 'using only the home office net income', 'adding total sales of both units',
   1, 'Combined net income equals the home office''s own net income plus the true branch net income, where true branch income reflects the realized overvaluation adjustment.', 2),
  ('AFAR', 'Home Office & Branch Accounting',
   'In preparing combined financial statements, which pair of accounts is eliminated against each other?',
   'Sales and Cost of Goods Sold', 'Cash and Accounts Receivable', 'Investment in Branch and Home Office', 'Allowance for Overvaluation and Sales',
   2, 'The reciprocal accounts Investment in Branch (home office books) and Home Office (branch books) are eliminated against each other in the combined financial statements.', 1),
  ('AFAR', 'Home Office & Branch Accounting',
   'Volga Home Office reported its own net income of P600,000. Its branch reported net income of P220,000, and the realized overvaluation for the year was P80,000. The combined net income is:',
   'P600,000', 'P820,000', 'P900,000', 'P980,000',
   2, 'True branch net income = P220,000 + P80,000 = P300,000. Combined net income = P600,000 + P300,000 = P900,000.', 2)
)
insert into public.questions (topic_id, stem, choices, correct_index, explanation, difficulty)
select t.id, q.stem, jsonb_build_array(q.a, q.b, q.c, q.d), q.correct_index, q.explanation, q.difficulty
from q join t on t.code = q.subject_code and lower(t.name) = lower(q.topic)
where not exists (select 1 from public.questions x where x.stem = q.stem);

-- ===== afar-batch-002 =====
-- Generated from content/afar-batch-002.csv by scripts/csv-to-seed-sql.mjs — do not edit by hand.
-- Idempotent: skips any question whose stem already exists.
with t as (
  select tp.id, tp.name, s.code from public.topics tp
  join public.subjects s on s.id = tp.subject_id
),
q(subject_code, topic, stem, a, b, c, d, correct_index, explanation, difficulty) as (values
  ('AFAR', 'Business Combinations',
   'Under PFRS 3, which of the following costs incurred in a business combination is expensed as incurred rather than included in the consideration transferred?',
   'Legal and due-diligence advisory fees', 'Fair value of contingent consideration', 'Fair value of shares issued to former owners', 'Cash paid to the acquiree owners',
   0, 'Acquisition-related costs such as legal, advisory, accounting, and valuation fees are expensed in the period incurred under PFRS 3. They are not part of consideration transferred.', 1),
  ('AFAR', 'Business Combinations',
   'Pine Corp acquired all net assets of Oak Corp for P5,000,000 cash. The fair value of Oak identifiable net assets was P4,300,000. How much goodwill arises?',
   'P700,000', 'P0', 'P4,300,000', 'P5,000,000',
   0, 'Goodwill = consideration transferred P5,000,000 − fair value of net identifiable assets P4,300,000 = P700,000.', 1),
  ('AFAR', 'Business Combinations',
   'Maple Inc issued 100,000 of its shares with a fair value of P40 each to acquire Birch Co. Direct share-issuance costs of P150,000 were paid in cash. How is the P150,000 accounted for?',
   'Added to goodwill', 'Expensed in profit or loss', 'Deducted from share premium (equity)', 'Capitalized as an intangible asset',
   2, 'Costs to issue equity instruments are deducted from equity (share premium) under PFRS 3 and PAS 32, not expensed and not added to goodwill.', 1),
  ('AFAR', 'Business Combinations',
   'Cedar Corp acquired 100% of Elm Corp by transferring cash of P3,000,000 and agreeing to pay an additional P500,000 if Elm meets an earnings target; the fair value of this contingent consideration at acquisition is P420,000. Total consideration transferred is:',
   'P3,000,000', 'P3,500,000', 'P3,420,000', 'P3,920,000',
   2, 'Consideration transferred includes contingent consideration at its acquisition-date fair value: P3,000,000 + P420,000 = P3,420,000. The undiscounted maximum P500,000 is not used.', 2),
  ('AFAR', 'Business Combinations',
   'Willow Corp acquired 80% of Ash Corp. Consideration transferred was P4,000,000; the fair value of the 20% NCI was P950,000; fair value of Ash identifiable net assets was P4,500,000. Goodwill under the full (fair value) method is:',
   'P0', 'P500,000', 'P450,000', 'P950,000',
   2, 'Goodwill (full) = consideration P4,000,000 + NCI at FV P950,000 − FV of net identifiable assets P4,500,000 = P450,000.', 2),
  ('AFAR', 'Business Combinations',
   'Using the same facts (consideration P4,000,000 for 80%; FV of net identifiable assets P4,500,000), goodwill under the partial (proportionate NCI) method is:',
   'P400,000', 'P450,000', 'P500,000', 'P900,000',
   0, 'Partial goodwill: NCI = 20% x P4,500,000 = P900,000. Goodwill = P4,000,000 + P900,000 − P4,500,000 = P400,000. Only the parent share of goodwill is recognized.', 2),
  ('AFAR', 'Business Combinations',
   'Spruce Corp acquired all of Fir Corp for cash of P2,800,000 when the fair value of Fir identifiable net assets was P3,100,000. The difference is:',
   'Goodwill of P300,000', 'Deferred and amortized over 10 years', 'A bargain purchase gain of P300,000 recognized in OCI', 'A bargain purchase gain of P300,000 recognized in profit or loss',
   3, 'When net identifiable assets exceed consideration, a bargain purchase gain of P3,100,000 − P2,800,000 = P300,000 is recognized in profit or loss after reassessment.', 2),
  ('AFAR', 'Business Combinations',
   'During the measurement period, the acquirer obtains new information about facts existing at acquisition date that increases the fair value of an acquired building by P200,000. The proper treatment is to:',
   'Recognize a P200,000 gain in profit or loss', 'Ignore it as a post-combination event', 'Recognize P200,000 in OCI', 'Retrospectively adjust goodwill downward by P200,000',
   3, 'Measurement-period adjustments for facts existing at acquisition date are recognized retrospectively; increasing the asset reduces goodwill by P200,000.', 1),
  ('AFAR', 'Business Combinations',
   'Holly Corp previously held a 30% interest in Berry Corp carried at P900,000; its fair value on the date Holly acquires the remaining 70% is P1,050,000. In the step acquisition, Holly must:',
   'Ignore the difference', 'Add P150,000 to share premium', 'Recognize P150,000 directly in retained earnings', 'Recognize a P150,000 remeasurement gain in profit or loss',
   3, 'In a business combination achieved in stages, the previously held equity interest is remeasured to fair value with the resulting P1,050,000 − P900,000 = P150,000 gain recognized in profit or loss.', 2),
  ('AFAR', 'Business Combinations',
   'Olive Corp acquires 70% of Date Corp by transferring cash of P2,100,000. The fair value of the 30% NCI is P850,000, and the previously-held interest was nil. Fair value of Date identifiable net assets is P2,600,000. Goodwill (full method) is:',
   'P0', 'P350,000', 'P500,000', 'P850,000',
   1, 'Goodwill = consideration P2,100,000 + NCI at FV P850,000 − FV net identifiable assets P2,600,000 = P350,000.', 2),
  ('AFAR', 'Business Combinations',
   'In a business combination, the acquirer is generally the combining entity that:',
   'Has the smaller fair value of net assets', 'Obtains control of the other entity', 'Issues the fewer shares', 'Is legally dissolved',
   1, 'Under PFRS 3 and PFRS 10, the acquirer is the entity that obtains control of the acquiree, regardless of legal form.', 1),
  ('AFAR', 'Business Combinations',
   'Lime Corp transferred consideration of P6,000,000 for 100% of Lemon Corp. Identifiable assets had a fair value of P7,200,000 and liabilities assumed a fair value of P2,400,000. Goodwill is:',
   'P1,200,000', 'P1,800,000', 'P3,600,000', 'P4,800,000',
   0, 'FV of net identifiable assets = P7,200,000 − P2,400,000 = P4,800,000. Goodwill = P6,000,000 − P4,800,000 = P1,200,000.', 2),
  ('AFAR', 'Business Combinations',
   'Grape Corp issued 50,000 shares (par P10, fair value P38) plus paid P400,000 cash to acquire Plum Corp. Consideration transferred is:',
   'P400,000', 'P900,000', 'P2,300,000', 'P1,900,000',
   2, 'Shares are measured at fair value: 50,000 x P38 = P1,900,000, plus cash P400,000 = P2,300,000. Par value is not used to measure consideration.', 2),
  ('AFAR', 'Business Combinations',
   'An in-process research and development project of the acquiree that meets the definition of an identifiable intangible asset is:',
   'Always expensed at acquisition', 'Recognized separately from goodwill at fair value', 'Included within goodwill', 'Recognized only if internally generated by the acquirer',
   1, 'An identifiable intangible asset such as acquired in-process R&D is recognized separately from goodwill at its acquisition-date fair value.', 1),
  ('AFAR', 'Business Combinations',
   'Kiwi Corp acquired 90% of Mango Corp for P4,800,000. Fair value of identifiable net assets was P5,500,000, and NCI is measured at proportionate share. The result is:',
   'Goodwill of P150,000', 'Bargain purchase gain of P150,000', 'Goodwill of P700,000', 'Bargain purchase gain of P700,000',
   1, 'NCI (proportionate) = 10% x P5,500,000 = P550,000. Consideration P4,800,000 + NCI P550,000 = P5,350,000, less FV net identifiable assets P5,500,000 = negative P150,000, recognized as a bargain purchase gain of P150,000 in profit or loss.', 3),
  ('AFAR', 'Business Combinations',
   'Which item is NOT part of the consideration transferred in a business combination?',
   'Cash paid to former owners', 'Fair value of equity instruments issued', 'Fair value of contingent consideration', 'Reimbursement of the acquiree employees future salaries',
   3, 'Future employee salaries relate to post-combination services and are expensed as incurred, not part of consideration transferred.', 1),
  ('AFAR', 'Business Combinations',
   'Banana Corp acquired all of Cherry Corp. Book value of Cherry net assets was P3,000,000; an item of equipment was undervalued by P400,000 and an unrecorded patent had a fair value of P250,000. Fair value of identifiable net assets is:',
   'P3,000,000', 'P3,400,000', 'P3,650,000', 'P3,250,000',
   2, 'FV of net identifiable assets = book value P3,000,000 + equipment understatement P400,000 + patent P250,000 = P3,650,000.', 2),
  ('AFAR', 'Business Combinations',
   'If contingent consideration classified as a liability is remeasured after the measurement period and its fair value increases by P80,000, the change is:',
   'Recognized in profit or loss', 'Adjusted against goodwill', 'Recognized in OCI', 'Adjusted against share premium',
   0, 'Contingent consideration classified as a financial liability is remeasured to fair value at each reporting date, with changes recognized in profit or loss (not goodwill).', 1),
  ('AFAR', 'Business Combinations',
   'Apple Corp acquired 75% of Pear Corp for P9,000,000. The implied fair value of Pear as a whole based on this price is:',
   'P6,750,000', 'P9,000,000', 'P12,000,000', 'P11,250,000',
   2, 'Implied total fair value = P9,000,000 / 75% = P12,000,000. This grosses the 75% price up to 100%.', 2),
  ('AFAR', 'Business Combinations',
   'Under PFRS 3, goodwill recognized in a business combination is subsequently:',
   'Amortized over its useful life', 'Amortized over a maximum of 20 years', 'Not amortized but tested for impairment at least annually', 'Revalued upward when fair value rises',
   2, 'Goodwill is not amortized; it is tested for impairment at least annually under PAS 36, and impairment losses are not reversed.', 1),
  ('AFAR', 'Business Combinations',
   'Coco Corp pays P3,200,000 for 80% of Nut Corp. Fair value of identifiable net assets is P3,400,000, and NCI is measured at its proportionate share. Goodwill is:',
   'P480,000', 'P680,000', 'P200,000', 'P0',
   0, 'NCI (proportionate) = 20% x P3,400,000 = P680,000. Goodwill = consideration P3,200,000 + NCI P680,000 − FV net identifiable assets P3,400,000 = P480,000.', 3),
  ('AFAR', 'Business Combinations',
   'When the acquirer measures NCI at fair value rather than at the proportionate share of net identifiable assets, the effect is generally to:',
   'Decrease total recognized goodwill', 'Have no effect on goodwill', 'Increase total recognized goodwill', 'Eliminate goodwill entirely',
   2, 'Measuring NCI at fair value recognizes the NCI share of goodwill (full goodwill), so total recognized goodwill is higher than under the proportionate method.', 1),
  ('AFAR', 'Business Combinations',
   'Tea Corp issued bonds with a fair value of P2,500,000 and paid cash of P700,000 to acquire Bean Corp, whose identifiable net assets had a fair value of P3,000,000. Goodwill is:',
   'P200,000', 'P500,000', 'P700,000', 'P0',
   0, 'Consideration = bonds at FV P2,500,000 + cash P700,000 = P3,200,000. Goodwill = P3,200,000 − P3,000,000 = P200,000.', 2),
  ('AFAR', 'Business Combinations',
   'Which of the following best describes a reverse acquisition?',
   'The acquiree is the larger entity', 'Goodwill is never recognized', 'The legal acquirer is identified as the accounting acquiree', 'The combination is reversed in the next period',
   2, 'In a reverse acquisition, the entity that issues shares (legal acquirer) is identified as the accounting acquiree, while the legal subsidiary is the accounting acquirer.', 1),
  ('AFAR', 'Business Combinations',
   'Salt Corp acquired 100% of Pepper Corp for P8,000,000 cash. Identifiable assets at fair value were P9,500,000 and liabilities assumed at fair value were P2,200,000. The combination results in:',
   'Goodwill of P700,000', 'Bargain purchase gain of P700,000', 'Goodwill of P1,500,000', 'Bargain purchase gain of P1,500,000',
   0, 'FV of net identifiable assets = P9,500,000 − P2,200,000 = P7,300,000. Goodwill = P8,000,000 − P7,300,000 = P700,000.', 2),
  ('AFAR', 'Consolidated Financial Statements',
   'Parent Co owns 80% of Sub Co. For the year, Sub reported net income of P1,000,000 with no fair-value differential amortization. The share of profit attributable to NCI is:',
   'P0', 'P1,000,000', 'P800,000', 'P200,000',
   3, 'NCI share of profit = 20% x P1,000,000 = P200,000. The remaining P800,000 is attributable to the owners of the parent.', 1),
  ('AFAR', 'Consolidated Financial Statements',
   'Parent Co owns 75% of Sub Co. Sub reported net income of P1,200,000. At acquisition an equipment fair-value excess of P300,000 is being amortized over 5 years. NCI share of profit is:',
   'P285,000', 'P300,000', 'P225,000', 'P315,000',
   0, 'Annual FV amortization = P300,000 / 5 = P60,000. Adjusted subsidiary profit = P1,200,000 − P60,000 = P1,140,000. NCI share = 25% x P1,140,000 = P285,000.', 2),
  ('AFAR', 'Consolidated Financial Statements',
   'During the year, Parent sold inventory to its wholly owned Sub for P500,000 (cost P350,000). At year-end Sub still holds 40% of these goods. The unrealized profit to be eliminated is:',
   'P150,000', 'P200,000', 'P90,000', 'P60,000',
   3, 'Total intercompany gross profit = P500,000 − P350,000 = P150,000. Unrealized portion = 40% still in ending inventory x P150,000 = P60,000.', 2),
  ('AFAR', 'Consolidated Financial Statements',
   'Parent sold goods to its 70%-owned Sub at a markup; ending intercompany inventory contains unrealized profit of P100,000 (downstream sale). The amount of unrealized profit allocated to NCI is:',
   'P0', 'P30,000', 'P70,000', 'P100,000',
   0, 'In a downstream sale, the full unrealized profit is borne by the parent (seller). None is allocated to NCI, so the NCI share is P0.', 1),
  ('AFAR', 'Consolidated Financial Statements',
   'Sub (70% owned) sold goods to Parent; ending intercompany inventory contains unrealized profit of P100,000 (upstream sale). The portion of the eliminated unrealized profit allocated to NCI is:',
   'P0', 'P100,000', 'P70,000', 'P30,000',
   3, 'In an upstream sale, the unrealized profit is in the seller (subsidiary). The NCI bears its share: 30% x P100,000 = P30,000.', 2),
  ('AFAR', 'Consolidated Financial Statements',
   'Parent and Sub had total separate sales of P9,000,000 and P5,000,000 respectively. Intercompany sales during the year were P1,200,000. Consolidated sales are:',
   'P14,000,000', 'P12,800,000', 'P15,200,000', 'P13,800,000',
   1, 'Consolidated sales = P9,000,000 + P5,000,000 − P1,200,000 intercompany = P12,800,000. Intercompany sales are eliminated in full.', 2),
  ('AFAR', 'Consolidated Financial Statements',
   'Parent sold equipment to Sub for P800,000; its carrying amount was P650,000. In the consolidation working papers in the year of sale, the intercompany gain to be eliminated is:',
   'P150,000', 'P800,000', 'P650,000', 'P0',
