   1, 'Applied P480,000 is less than actual P510,000, so overhead is underapplied by P30,000 (a debit balance in the overhead account).', 2),
  ('AFAR', 'Cost Accounting Systems',
   'If overhead is underapplied by an immaterial P30,000 at year-end, the usual disposition is to:',
   'Capitalize it as an asset', 'Close it to cost of goods sold, increasing COGS by P30,000', 'Close it to sales', 'Defer it to next year',
   1, 'Immaterial under/overapplied overhead is closed to cost of goods sold; underapplied overhead increases COGS by P30,000.', 2),
  ('AFAR', 'Cost Accounting Systems',
   'A predetermined overhead rate is computed as estimated overhead divided by estimated activity. Estimated overhead is P900,000 and estimated machine hours are 60,000. The rate per machine hour is:',
