   2, 'A joint venture for construction projects (and one for energy operations under a service contract with the government) is NOT treated as a taxable corporation. The co-venturers report their respective shares in their own returns.', 2),
  ('TAX', 'Income Tax: Partnerships, Estates & Trusts',
   'A joint venture formed by two corporations to operate a chain of retail stores (not construction or energy operations) is:',
