   1, 'A joint venture that is not for construction or for energy or petroleum operations under a government service contract is treated as a taxable corporation subject to corporate income tax.', 2),
  ('TAX', 'Income Tax: Partnerships, Estates & Trusts',
   'Two heirs inherited a parcel of land and merely held it as co-owners while collecting rent, dividing the income between them without reinvesting. The co-ownership is:',
