   0, 'A co-ownership for the mere preservation of inherited property and collection of its income is generally not a taxable entity. Each co-owner reports his respective share of the income in his own return.', 2),
  ('TAX', 'Income Tax: Partnerships, Estates & Trusts',
   'Two heirs who inherited property continued to invest the rental income jointly in additional income-producing ventures for profit. The arrangement may be treated as:',
