   1, 'When co-owners do not divide the income but instead reinvest it in additional income-producing ventures for profit, the co-ownership is converted into an unregistered partnership taxable as a corporation.', 3),
  ('TAX', 'Income Tax: Partnerships, Estates & Trusts',
   'An estate under judicial settlement is, for income tax purposes:',
   'A separate taxpayer using the graduated income tax table', 'Never a taxpayer', 'Taxed as a corporation at 25% RCIT', 'Subject to a 6% final tax',
   0, 'An estate under judicial settlement is a separate taxpayer and computes its income tax using the graduated table applicable to individuals during the period of settlement.', 2),
  ('TAX', 'Income Tax: Partnerships, Estates & Trusts',
   'An estate under judicial settlement earned net income of P800,000 and distributed P300,000 to an heir during the year. In computing the taxable income of the estate, the P300,000 distributed to the heir is:',
   'Deductible by the estate and taxable to the heir', 'Not deductible by the estate', 'A final-tax item at 10%', 'Exempt to both estate and heir',
   0, 'Income of the estate that is properly paid or credited to an heir during the year is deductible by the estate and is taxable to the heir who receives it, avoiding double taxation of the same income.', 2),
  ('TAX', 'Income Tax: Partnerships, Estates & Trusts',
   'An irrevocable trust is treated as:',
