   0, 'While a mortgage is valid between the parties even if unregistered, it binds and prejudices third persons only from the time it is registered in the Registry of Property.', 2),
  ('RFBT', 'Credit Transactions: Pledge, Mortgage & Guaranty',
   'Following an extrajudicial foreclosure of a real estate mortgage under Act No. 3135, the mortgagor right of redemption generally lasts:',
   'Ninety days from the auction date', 'One year from the registration of the certificate of sale', 'Until the mortgagee resells the property', 'There is no redemption in extrajudicial foreclosure',
   1, 'In extrajudicial foreclosure under Act No. 3135, the mortgagor has a right of redemption of one year reckoned from the registration of the certificate of sale; in judicial foreclosure, what exists is the equity of redemption before confirmation.', 2),
  ('RFBT', 'Credit Transactions: Pledge, Mortgage & Guaranty',
   'Which document is essential to the validity of a chattel mortgage and distinguishes it from a pledge?',
   'A public auction notice posted in advance', 'A deposit of the chattel with a third person', 'An affidavit of good faith stating the mortgage is made to secure a just obligation', 'A guarantor solidary undertaking',
   2, 'A chattel mortgage requires an affidavit of good faith attesting that it is made to secure a just and valid obligation; the chattel stays with the mortgagor, unlike in pledge where delivery is required.', 2),
  ('RFBT', 'Credit Transactions: Pledge, Mortgage & Guaranty',
   'Dina is a guarantor, not a surety, for Ben debt to Ana. When Ben defaults, Ana sues Dina directly. Dina may:',
   'Be held solidarily liable immediately like a surety', 'Demand that the debt be cut in half', 'Refuse to pay forever because guaranty is gratuitous', 'Invoke the benefit of excussion and require Ana to first exhaust Ben property',
   3, 'A guarantor liability is subsidiary; by the benefit of excussion he can require the creditor to first exhaust the debtor properties before proceeding against him, a defense unavailable to a surety who is solidarily bound.', 2),
  ('RFBT', 'Credit Transactions: Pledge, Mortgage & Guaranty',
   'The benefit of excussion is LOST and the guarantor becomes liable as if no such benefit existed when:',
   'The guarantor expressly renounces it or binds himself solidarily with the debtor', 'The principal obligation is merely reduced', 'The creditor sends a single demand letter', 'The debt is secured by a separate pledge',
   0, 'Excussion is lost when, among others, the guarantor renounces it, binds himself solidarily, the debtor is insolvent, or cannot be sued within the Philippines; mere reduction or demand does not remove it.', 2),
  ('RFBT', 'Credit Transactions: Pledge, Mortgage & Guaranty',
   'A guarantor who pays the creditor after the debtor default is entitled to:',
