  ('RFBT', 'Negotiable Instruments',
   'An instrument is payable to bearer when, among others, it is:',
   'Payable to the order of a named, existing payee', 'Indorsed specially to a named indorsee', 'Payable to the order of a person known by the maker to be fictitious', 'Made payable to a specified person only',
   2, 'An instrument is payable to bearer when, among others, it is payable to a fictitious or non-existing person and that fact is known to the person making it so payable; such an instrument is negotiated by mere delivery.', 1),
  ('RFBT', 'Negotiable Instruments',
   'A bearer instrument is specially indorsed by the holder to Carlo. To further negotiate it, the next holder must:',
