   1, 'Once bearer, always bearer: an instrument originally payable to bearer remains negotiable by mere delivery despite a subsequent special indorsement, although the special indorser is liable to those who take by delivery.', 3),
  ('RFBT', 'Negotiable Instruments',
   'The principal practical difference between negotiation and ordinary assignment of an instrument is that:',
   'Assignment passes better title than negotiation', 'Negotiation always requires a notarized deed', 'Only assignment can transfer a bearer instrument', 'A holder in due course by negotiation can take free of personal defenses, while an assignee takes subject to all defenses',
   3, 'Negotiation can vest a holder in due course with rights free from personal defenses, whereas an assignee merely steps into the assignor shoes and takes subject to all defenses available against the assignor.', 2),
  ('RFBT', 'Negotiable Instruments',
